properties.areaDesc: Chesapeake Bay from Sandy Point to North Beach MD; Patuxent River to Broomes Island MD; Chesapeake Bay from North Beach to Drum Point MD; Eastern Bay; Tidal Potomac from Key Bridge to Indian Head MD; Tidal Potomac from Indian Head to Cobb Island MD; Choptank River to Cambridge MD and the Little Choptank River
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 6 at 10:18AM EST until February 7 at 6:00PM EST by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 15 to 20 kt with gusts up to 30 kt expected.

* WHERE...Tidal Potomac River from Key Bridge to Cobb Island MD,
Patuxent River to Broomes Island MD, Choptank River to
Cambridge MD and the Little Choptank River, Chesapeake Bay
from North Beach to Drum Point MD, Chesapeake Bay from Sandy
Point to North Beach MD, and Eastern Bay.

* WHEN...From 9 AM to 6 PM EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 6 PM EST FRIDAY
